Package org.hibernate.sql.ast.tree.spi.from Description

Models the concepts in the SQL <from clause>.

The lowest level of this modeling is the TableReference contract which models a table as known to the Hibernate persisters. This might be a physical table or a derived table (Hibernate subselect mapping).

TableSpecifications are grouped into a TableGroup representing all of the TableSpecifications originating from a particular persister reference. Think of this piece as the bridge between persister references in a query and the tables represented by that persister reference.

Finally TableSpecificationGroups are themselves grouped into a TableSpace. todo : example of TableSpace e.g. ... from Entity1, Entity2
